Abstract = {{A randomized forecasting method based on the generation of ensembles of
   entropy-optimal forecasting trajectories is developed. The latter are
   generated by randomized dynamic regression models containing random
   parameters, measurement noises, and a random input. The probability
   density functions of random parameters and measurement noises are
   estimated using real data within the randomized machine learning
   procedure. The ensembles of forecasting trajectories are generated by
   the sampling of the entropy-optimal probability distributions. This
   procedure is used for the randomized prediction of the daily electrical
   load of a regional power system. A stochastic oscillatory dynamic
   regression model is designed. One-, two-, and three-day forecasts of the
