   supply, hydropower, as an important clean energy, plays a bigger role
   than before. It is shown that hydropower has immense potential and is
   the best choice to cater for the energy demand in Southeast Asia. In
   this work, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand and Myanmar are selected to
   analyze their hydropower development. This work introduces the status of
   hydropower resources, the current situation of hydropower development
   and the main distribution of hydropower stations in the four countries.
