Abstract = {{With the increase of renewable energy permeability and the development
   of distributed grid, energy storage plays an increasingly important role
   in the power system. A lot of studies have shown that energy storage can
   already be economically feasible. However, most previous studies
   concentrated on the value of energy storage in the free electricity
   market. In China, the power grid monopolizes the process of electricity
   transmission, distribution and retail, and the feed-in tariff and retail
   prices of electricity are regulated by government. It is difficult to
   analyze the application value of energy storage for China's electricity
   due to the lacking of data. The major contribution of this paper is to
   evaluate the application value according to the data of a provincial
   power grid. The results support the argument that energy storage can
